				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/pawelnow/"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1223e85b4edc632ab5b6d8458327e95ed635758e8dd592b3ae4130ee1303bbb7?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1223e85b4edc632ab5b6d8458327e95ed635758e8dd592b3ae4130ee1303bbb7?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/pawelnow/" class="reviewer-name">PaweÅ‚ Nowacki <small>(pawelnow)</small></a> on <span class="review-date">mÃ¤rts 29, 2023</span>			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="review-body"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I am very happy with the plugin's operation - it is extremely easy to use and does not cause any problems.<br />Works with WordPress Multisite great!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>However, there is a feature missing from the plugin that has already been popping up on the web, namely support for reciprocal hreflang (return tag: which is missing Missing x-default).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When I audit any page with this plugin, I get "Missing reciprocal hreflang (no return-tag)", you can find info at Ahrefs site ""Missing reciprocal hreflang (no return-tag)" error in Site Audit"</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I will be very grateful if this functionality is added :)<br />As I can see this needs to add one line of code :)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Greeting from Poland<br />PaweÅ‚</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
